  "xp_source": "Per-round XP is NOT in the BTD Mod Helper game data dump (round files store only bloon composition + timing; bloon models store no xp/cash). BTD6 awards a FIXED XP amount per round number, independent of bloons popped: XP(r) = 20r+20 (r<=20) / 40(r-20)+420 (21<=r<=50) / 90(r-50)+1620 (r>=51). Validated against bloonswiki's own 'Base XP' column (List_of_rounds_in_BTD6) at every band boundary. base_xp is the Beginner (x1.0), non-freeplay amount before Monkey Knowledge; multiply by difficulty_multipliers and freeplay_multipliers as needed. Tower XP is then split among tower types by share of cash invested (gameplay-dependent, not stored).",
